# Frontend Rules — web

## Scope

- `src/**`

## Rules

- Do not change backend contracts.
- Reuse existing UI components and patterns.
- Handle loading, error, empty, and success states.

## List pagination

See `planning-poker-dev/docs/development/LISTS.md`.

| Data source | Hook | Network on «Показать ещё» |
|---|---|---|
| CMS list API (`/cms/...?limit&cursor`) | `useCmsList` → `useProgressiveList` | Yes — next page only |
| Snapshot / board JSON already loaded | `useListDisplayWindow` | No — reveals next slice in memory |

- First page size: **`LIST_PAGE_SIZE` (10)** — `src/shared/listPaging.ts`.
- UI footer: `LoadMoreFooter` or `ScopeIncrementalFooter`.
- Do not auto-fetch all pages; only explicit user action (or documented print/export).

## Output

1. UI behavior implemented
2. States covered
3. Files changed
4. Manual checks
5. Risks
